ObjectStates.Name: Bag
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
allUpgrades = {}

allPilots = {}
pilotsBag = nil
pilotsBagName = 'Pilot Cards Bag'
conflictSets = {}
choiceSets = {}
confCount = 0

allModels = {}
modelLGSflag = {}
modelsBag = nil
modelsBagName = 'Ship Models Bag'

note = nil
notecardName = 'Spawn Me'

dialsBagName = 'Dials Bag'
dialsBag = {}
dialsToSpawn = {}

function ClearButtonsPatch(obj)
    local buttons = obj.getButtons()
    if buttons ~= nil then
        for k,but in pairs(buttons) do
            obj.removeButton(but.index)
        end
    end
end

-- ON LOAD --
function onload()

    -- For each stored upgrade:
    for k,v in pairs(self.getObjects()) do

        -- Update particular upgrade count
        if allUpgrades[v['name']] == nil then
            allUpgrades[v['name']] = v['guid']
        else
            print('Dupl card!' .. v['name'] .. 'E')
        end

    end


    -- INITIALIZE BUTTON
    button = {}

    button.click_function = 'init'
    button.function_owner = self
    button.label = 'Initialize' -- 20
    button.position = {0, 0.5, 3}
    button.rotation = {0, 0, 0}
    button.width = 3000
    button.height = 800
    button.font_size = 20000

    self.createButton(button)

end
-- END ON LOAD --

-- FUNCTIONS FOR OTHER BAGS
function savePilots( pilots )
    allPilots = pilots
end

function saveModels( models )
    allModels = models
end
-- END FUNCTIONS FOR OTHER BAGS

-- INITIALIZE BAG
function init()

    -- Find and save other bags:
    for k,obj in pairs(getAllObjects()) do
        if obj.getName() == modelsBagName and obj.getDescription() == 'Unassigned' then modelsBag = obj obj.setDescription('OK!') end
        if obj.getName() == pilotsBagName and obj.getDescription() == 'Unassigned' then pilotsBag = obj obj.setDescription('OK!') end
        if obj.getName() == dialsBagName and obj.getDescription() == 'Unassigned' then dialsBag = obj obj.setDescription('OK!') end
    end

    -- Tell other bags to pass their contents here:
    if pilotsBag == nil or modelsBag == nil then
        fatalError('Others bags not found! Make sure paste a new set of bags every time you\'re building a new squad')
    else
        callLuaFunctionInOtherScriptWithParams(pilotsBag, 'passContents', {self}) -- 50
        callLuaFunctionInOtherScriptWithParams(modelsBag, 'passContents', {self})
        note = allUpgrades[notecardName]

        -- Fill table with pilot names designated as conflicting (v1, v2, v3 etc at the end of the name)
        for k, pilot in pairs(allPilots) do
            local name = k:match('[\'%w%s%-.]+[%s]v[%d]')
            if name ~= nil then
                local commonName = name:gsub('[%s]v[%d]', '')
                local commonIndex = name:sub(-1, -1)
                if conflictSets[commonName] == nil then conflictSets[commonName] = {} end
                table.insert(conflictSets[commonName], pilot)
                -- table entry with COMMON NAME as KEY contains GUIDs of pilots with same common name
            end
        end

        -- Spawn note for parsing squad:
        local pos = self.getPosition()
        local rot = self.getRotation()
        local params = {}
        params.guid = note
        params.position = {pos['x']-(math.sin(math.rad(rot['y']))*8), pos['y']+2, pos['z']-(math.cos(math.rad(rot['y']))*8)}
        params.rotation = {self.getRotation()[1], self.getRotation()[2]+180, self.getRotation()[3]}
        note = self.takeObject(params)

        -- Change button to spawning function:
        self.clearButtons()
        ClearButtonsPatch(self)
        button.click_function = 'spawnMe'
        button.label = 'Spawn it!'
        self.createButton(button)

    end
    -- END IF OTHER BAGS OK

end

-- END INITIALIZE BAG

-- SPAWN SET OF PILOT CARDS WITH BUTTONS FOR CHOICE WHEN MULTIPLE PILOTS HAVE SAME NAME
-- cShipname : common name, cShipPos : position for ship model
-- only works for 2 conflicting cards, adjust position for more
function spawnConflictChoice(cShipName, cShipPos)

    confCount = confCount + 1 -- increase global conflict/choice counter
    local cPos = {}
    cPos['x'] = cShipPos['x']
    cPos['y'] = cShipPos['y']
    cPos['z'] = cShipPos['z']
    cPos['x'] = cPos['x'] - (2.35/2)
    choiceSets[cShipName] = {}

    -- spawn every conflicting pilot card with a button
    for k, pil in pairs(conflictSets[cShipName]) do
        local newChoice = pilotsBag.takeObject({guid = pil, position = cPos, rotation = self.getRotation()})
        newChoice.setVar('cInd', k)               -- save card index
        newChoice.setVar('cTrueName', cShipName)  -- save common name
        table.insert(choiceSets[cShipName], newChoice) -- fill a table containing all spawned cards for a conflict
        local button = {}
        button.click_function = 'chooseCard'
        button.function_owner = self
        button.label = 'Choose'
        button.position = {0, 0.5, 0 - (2.5*math.cos(math.rad(self.getRotation()['y'])))}
        button.rotation = {0, 0, 0}
        button.width = 1000
        button.height = 400
        button.font_size = 200
        newChoice.createButton(button)
        if cPos['x'] < cShipPos['x'] then cPos['x'] = cPos['x'] + 2.35
        else cPos['x'] = cPos['x'] - 2.35 cPos['z'] = cPos['z'] + (3.25*math.sin(math.rad(self.getRotation()['y']))) end
    end

end

-- CHOOSE A CARD FORM THE CONFLICT, DESTROY OTHERS
function chooseCard(clickedCard, dummy)

    -- destroy every other card from the respective conflict table
    for k,card in pairs(choiceSets[clickedCard.getVar('cTrueName')]) do
        if card ~= clickedCard then card.destruct() end
    end

    -- save the direction of the card to ship position offset, expand choice (spawn ship model, adjust names)
    local dir = ((clickedCard.getVar('cInd'))-1.5)*-2
    expandChoice(clickedCard, dir, clickedCard.getVar('cTrueName'))
end

function expandChoice(card, dir, trueName)
    --print(card.getName() .. ' ' .. trueName)
    mPos = card.getPosition()
    local modifiedName = card.getName()
    mPos['x'] = mPos['x'] + ((2.35/2)*dir)
    card.setPosition({card.getPosition()['x']+((2.35/2)*dir), 1, card.getPosition()['z']-4})
    if allModels[card.getName()] == nil then fatalError('In expandChoice: model named ' .. card.getName() .. ' not found') end
    nMod = modelsBag.takeObject({guid=allModels[card.getName()], position = mPos, rotation = card.getRotation()})
    table.insert(spawnedShips, nMod)
    card.setName(trueName)
    card.clearButtons()
    ClearButtonsPatch(card)
    nMod.setName(trueName)
    nMod.setPosition(mPos)
    nMod.setRotation(card.getRotation())
    --table.insert(spawnedShips, nMod)

    confCount = confCount - 1
    if confCount == 0 then
        spawnDials()
        spawnShields()
    end

    --[[
    if modelLGSflag[card.getName()] == 1 then
    nMod.setName(trueName .. ' LGS')
end
--]]
end

-- Function to replace character from string:
function replaceChar(pos, str, r)
    return str:sub(1, pos - 1) .. r .. str:sub(pos + 1, str:len())
end

function lastEl(itable)
    local num = 0
    for k in pairs(itable) do num = num + 1 end
    return num
end

-- MAIN SQUAD SPAWNING FUNCTION
function spawnMe()

    local desc = note.getDescription()
    local words = {}
    allShips = {}
    spawnedShips = {}
    local spawnedPCs = {}
    local listedShips = {}


    desc = desc:gsub('[%s]%([^%d][%w%s\']+%)', '')
    for word in desc:gmatch('[\u{201C}\u{201D}\u{2019}\'\"/%w%s%-%.]+[%s][+%(].') do
        --print(word)
        --if word:sub(-1, -1) == 'P' then word = word:sub(1, -3) word = word .. '+ ' end

        word = word:match('^%s*(.+)%s*.$')
        for i = 1, #word do
            local c = word:sub(i,i)
            if c == '\u{201C}' or c == '\u{201D}'
            then
                word = replaceChar(i, word, '"')
            end
            if c == '\u{2019}' then word = replaceChar(i, word, '\'') end
        end
        table.insert(words, word)
    end




    -- END PROCESSING DESCRIPTION

    -- SAVE SHIPS TO SHIP->UPGRADES TABLE
    -- Any duplicate ship is appended number in square brackets
    --local allShips = {}
    local nextship = true
    local ship = nil
    local upgrades = {}
    local lastShipNum
    for k,v in pairs(words) do
        if nextship == true then
            local shipTable = {}
            ship = v:sub(0, -3)
            shipTable[1] = ship
            shipTable[2] = {}
            --allShips[ship] = {}
            nextship = false
            if v:sub(-1, -1) == '(' then nextship = true end
            table.insert(allShips, shipTable)
        else
            table.insert(allShips[lastEl(allShips)][2], v:sub(0, -3))
            if v:sub(-1, -1) == '(' then nextship = true end
        end
    end
    --end
    -- END BUILDING SHIP->UPGRADES TABLES

    -- Count ships:
    shipN=0
    for k,v in pairs(allShips) do
        shipN = shipN + 1
    end

    -- SET SHIP PLACEMENT CONFIGURATION
    shipSpacing = 5.5
    shipPos = self.getPosition()
    shipPos['x'] = shipPos['x'] - ((shipN-1)*(shipSpacing*0.5))
    shipPos['y'] = shipPos['y'] + 0.5
    shipPos['z'] = shipPos['z'] - 5
    shipRot = self.getRotation()
    -- END SHIP PLACEMENT CONFIGURATION

    spawnedPairs = {}
    spawnedUpgrades = {}
    cloned = {}
    -- START MAIN SPAWNING LOOP
    for k,v in pairs(allShips) do

        -- Spawning ship model:
        local params = {}
        shipName = v[1]

        if conflictSets[shipName] == nil then
            if spawnedPairs[shipName] == nil then
                params.guid = allModels[shipName]
                if params.guid == nil then fatalError('In spawnMe, no conflict, first spawn: no model named ' .. shipName .. ' found') end
                newShip = modelsBag.takeObject(params)
                newShip.setPosition(shipPos)
                newShip.setRotation(shipRot)
                table.insert(spawnedShips, newShip)
                --if duplicate == true then newShip.setName(toName) end
                spawnedPairs[shipName] = {}
                spawnedPairs[shipName][1] = newShip
                -- Spawning pilot card:
                params2 = {}

                params2.guid = allPilots[shipName]
                if params2.guid == nil then fatalError('In spawnMe, no conflict, first spawn: no pilot card named ' .. shipName .. ' found') end
                newPilotCard = pilotsBag.takeObject(params2)
                newPilotCard.setName(newShip.getName())
                --spawnedPCs[newShip.getName()] = newPilotCard
                spawnedPairs[shipName][2] = newPilotCard
                spawnedPairs[shipName][3] = 1
                posPC = newShip.getPosition()
                posPC['z'] = posPC['z'] - 4
                rotPC = newShip.getRotation()
                newPilotCard.setPosition(posPC)
                newPilotCard.setRotation(rotPC)

            else
                newShip = spawnedPairs[shipName][1].clone({position = shipPos})
                newShip.setRotation(shipRot)
                table.insert(cloned, newShip)
                posPC = newShip.getPosition()
                posPC['z'] = posPC['z'] - 4
                rotPC = newShip.getRotation()
                newPilotCard = spawnedPairs[shipName][2].clone({position = posPC})
                newPilotCard.setName(newShip.getName())
                newPilotCard.setRotation(rotPC)
                if spawnedPairs[shipName][3] == 1 then
                    spawnedPairs[shipName][4] = spawnedPairs[shipName][1].getName()
                    spawnedPairs[shipName][1].setName(spawnedPairs[shipName][1].getName() .. ' 1')
                    spawnedPairs[shipName][2].setName(spawnedPairs[shipName][2].getName() .. ' 1')
                end
                spawnedPairs[shipName][3] = spawnedPairs[shipName][3] + 1
                newShip.setName(spawnedPairs[shipName][4] .. ' ' .. spawnedPairs[shipName][3])
                newPilotCard.setName(spawnedPairs[shipName][4] .. ' ' .. spawnedPairs[shipName][3])
                --[[
                if newPilotCard.getName():find('LGS') ~= nil then
                newPilotCard.setName(newPilotCard.getName():gsub(' LGS', ''))
            end
            --]]
        end
    else
        spawnConflictChoice(shipName, shipPos)
        posPC = {}
        posPC['x'] = shipPos['x']
        posPC['y'] = shipPos['y']
        posPC['z'] = shipPos['z']
        posPC['z'] = posPC['z'] - 4
    end

    -- Upgrade cards dimensions:
    -- 2.35 x 3.25 -- 1.175 x 1.625 PC
    -- 2.1 x 1.4 -- 1.05 x 0.7
    PCheight = 3.25
    PCwidth = 2.35
    UGheight = 2.1
    UGwidth = 1.4

    counter = 1

    local upgNum = 0
    for k2,v2 in pairs(allShips[k][2]) do upgNum = upgNum +1 end

    if upgNum == 1 then posPC['x'] = posPC['x']+UGwidth
    elseif upgNum == 2 then posPC['x'] = posPC['x']+(UGwidth/2) end

    for k2,v2 in pairs(allShips[k][2]) do
        if k2==1 then
            upgPos = posPC
            upgPos['x'] = upgPos['x'] - UGwidth
            upgPos['z'] = upgPos['z'] - PCheight/2 - UGheight/2
        else
            if counter == 3 then
                counter = 1
                upgPos['x'] = upgPos['x'] - 2*UGwidth
                upgPos['z'] = upgPos['z'] - UGheight
            else
                counter = counter + 1
                upgPos['x'] = upgPos['x'] + UGwidth
            end
        end
        upgName = v2
        --print('SU:' .. upgName .. ':' .. allUpgrades[upgName])
        if spawnedUpgrades[upgName] == nil then
            params3 = {}
            params3.guid = allUpgrades[upgName]
            if params3.guid == nil then fatalError('In spawnMe, first spawn: no upgrade card named ' .. upgName .. ' found') end
            newUpg = self.takeObject(params3)
            spawnedUpgrades[upgName] = newUpg
        else
            newUpg = spawnedUpgrades[upgName].clone({position = upgPos})
        end
        -- Spawning upgrade card:
        newUpg.setPosition(upgPos)
        newUpg.setRotation(shipRot)
    end
    -- END FOR EACH UPGRADE LOOP

    -- Set position for next ship model:
    shipPos['x'] = shipPos['x'] + shipSpacing



end
-- END FOR EACH SHIP LOOP

if confCount == 0 then spawnDials() spawnShields() end

end
-- END MAIN SPAWN FUNCTION

function spawnShields()
    shieldsToSpawn = {}
    for k, ship in pairs(spawnedShips) do
      --print('SS: ' .. ship.getName())
        local newShipModel = ship.getCustomObject()['mesh']
        for k,type in pairs(shipModelDatabase) do
            for k2, model in pairs(type) do
                if newShipModel == model then
                    table.insert(shieldsToSpawn, {type[2], ship})
                end
            end
        end
    end
    for k, ship in pairs(cloned) do
      --print('CS: ' .. ship.getName())
        local newShipModel = ship.getCustomObject()['mesh']
        for k,type in pairs(shipModelDatabase) do
            for k2, model in pairs(type) do
                if newShipModel == model then
                    table.insert(shieldsToSpawn, {type[2], ship})
                end
            end
        end
    end

    obj_type = {type='Custom_Model'}
    obj_params = {mesh='http://pastebin.com/raw.php?i=VjZhkJSi', diffuse='http://img4.fotos-hochladen.net/uploads/shieldq5cnl13vty.png', type=5, material=1}

    for k, info in pairs(shieldsToSpawn) do
        --print('Spawn ' .. info[1] .. ' shields on ' .. info[2].getName())
        local k = 0
        --print('P: ' .. info[2].getPosition()['x'] .. info[2].getPosition()['y'] .. info[2].getPosition()['z'])
        initPos = offset(info[2].getPosition(), {1.65, 0.1, -3})
        while k < info[1] do
            newShield = spawnObject(obj_type)
            newShield.setCustomObject(obj_params)
            local off = {math.floor(k/3)*0.8, 0, -0.9*(k%3)-math.floor(k/3)*0.45}
            --print('Off: ' .. off[1] .. ' ' .. off[2] .. ' ' .. off[3])
            newShield.setPosition(offset(initPos, off))
            newShield.setScale({0.375, 0.375, 0.375})
            k = k + 1
        end
    end
end

function spawnDials()

    self.clearButtons()
    ClearButtonsPatch(self)

    local allDials = {}
    for k,v in pairs(dialsBag.getObjects()) do
        allDials[v['name']] = v['guid']
    end

    dialsToSpawn = {}
    --spawnedDials = {}
    nDials = 0



    for k, ship in pairs(spawnedShips) do
        local newShipModel = ship.getCustomObject()['mesh']
        local found = false
        for k,type in pairs(shipModelDatabase) do
            for k2, model in pairs(type) do
                if newShipModel == model then
                    if dialsToSpawn[type[1]] ~= true then dialsToSpawn[type[1]] = true end
                    found = true
                    --table.insert(dialsToSpawn, {ship, type[1]})
                end
            end
        end
        if found == false then fatalError('In spawnDials,: no dials found for ' .. ship.getName()) end
    end

    for name,v in pairs(dialsToSpawn) do nDials = nDials + 1 end

    fDialPos = self.getPosition()

    --fDialRot['y'] = fDialRot['y'] + 45

        if allDials[name .. ' Refcard'] == nil then fatalError('In spawnDials: no reference card named \'' .. name .. ' Refcard\' found') end
        newDial = dialsBag.takeObject({guid = allDials[name .. ' Dials'], position = fDialPos})
        newDial.setPosition(fDialPos)
        fDialPos['x'] = fDialPos['x'] + 2
        newDial.setRotation(fDialRot)
        newRefCard = dialsBag.takeObject({guid = allDials[name .. ' Refcard'], position = refCardPos, rotation = refCardRot})
        newRefCard.setPosition(refCardPos)
        refCardPos['y'] = refCardPos['y'] + 0.1
        newRefCard.setRotation(refCardRot)
    end

    dName = dPair[2] .. ' Dials'

modelsBag.setPosition(offset(modelsBag.getPosition(), {0, 0.5, 5}))
pilotsBag.setPosition(offset(pilotsBag.getPosition(), {0, 0.5, 5}))

function offset(pos, off)
    nPos = {}
    nPos[1] = pos[1] + off[1]
    nPos[2] = pos[2] + off[2]
    nPos[3] = pos[3] + off[3]
    nPos['x'] = nPos[1]
    nPos['y'] = nPos[2]
    nPos['z'] = nPos[3]
    return nPos
end

function fatalError(desc)
    if(note ~= nil) then
        note.setName('FATAL ERROR')
        note.setDescription(desc)
    else
        print('Fatal error: ' .. desc)
    end
end

shipModelDatabase = {
    xWing = {'X-Wing', 2, 'https://paste.ee/r/54FLC', 'https://paste.ee/r/eAdkb', 'https://paste.ee/r/hxWah', 'https://paste.ee/r/ZxcTT', 'https://paste.ee/r/FfWNK', 'https://paste.ee/r/cwXlV'},
    yWingReb = {'Y-Wing Rebel', 3, 'https://paste.ee/r/MV6qP'},
    yt1300 = {'YT-1300', 5, 'https://paste.ee/r/kkPoB'},
    yt2400 = {'YT-2400', 5, 'https://paste.ee/r/Ff0vZ'},
    aWing = {'A-Wing', 2, 'https://paste.ee/r/tIdib', 'https://paste.ee/r/mow3U', 'https://paste.ee/r/ntg8n'},
    bWing = {'B-Wing', 5, 'https://paste.ee/r/8CtXr'},

ObjectStates.Name: Bag
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
allPilots = {}
loaded = false
pilotCount = {}

upgradesBag = nil

function onload()

for k,v in pairs(self.getObjects()) do
    if allPilots[v['name']] == nil then
      allPilots[v['name']] = v['guid']
    else
      print('Dupl card!'.. v['name'])
    end
end
loaded = true
end

function passContents(mainBag)
upgradesBag = mainBag[1]
--print('Bag:' .. upgradesBag.getName())
local empty = {}
if loaded == true then
callLuaFunctionInOtherScriptWithParams(upgradesBag, 'savePilots', allPilots)
else print('Too fast pilots') return empty
end
end

ContainedObjects.Name: Deck
ContainedObjects.LuaScript:
originPos = {}      -- position of the stack before laying out (left-bottom corner)
x_half = 0          -- which half of table X-axis-wise we play on (+1 or -1)
z_half = 0          -- which half of table Z-axis-wise we play on (+1 or -1)
kNum = 1            -- koiogran turn counter (for layout)

-- SPAWN FLIP AND LAYOUT BUTTONS
function onLoad()
    self.unlock()
    local button = {}
    button.click_function = 'init'
    button.function_owner = self
    button.label = 'Lay out'
    button.position = {0, -0.5, 0}
    button.rotation = {180, 180, 0}
    button.width = 1500
    button.height = 500
    button.font_size = 300
    self.createButton(button)
    button.width = 1800
    button.click_function = 'selfFlip'
    button.label = 'Flip to start'
    button.rotation = {0, 0, 0}
    button.position = {0, 0.5, 0}
    self.createButton(button)
end

function selfFlip()
    local sRot = self.getRotation()
    self.setRotation({sRot['x']+180, sRot['y']+180, sRot['z']})
end

-- RETURN POSITION BASED ON:
-- -- DESCRIPTION (WHICH MOVE IT IS)
-- -- "TURN LEFT ZERO" POSITION, OFFSET
-- -- DIAL SPACING - DEPENDENT ON SCALE
function decodePos(desc, te0pos, dialSpacing)
    dir = nil
    speed = nil
    type = nil
    if desc:sub(-1, -1) == 's' then
        type = 'seg'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(-2, -2))
        dir = desc:sub(-3, -3)
    elseif desc:sub(-1, -1) == 't' then
        type = 'tal'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(-2, -2))
        dir = desc:sub(-3, -3)
    elseif desc:sub(1, 1) == 'k' then
        type = 'koi'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(2, 2))
        dir = 's'
    elseif desc:sub(1, 1) == 's' then
        type = 's'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(2, 2))
        dir = 's'
    else
        type = desc:sub(1, 1)
        dir = desc:sub(2, 2)
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(3, 3))
    end

    outPos = {x=0, y=0.1, z=0}
    outPos['z'] = speed * dialSpacing
    if type == 's' then outPos['x'] = 0

    elseif type == 'seg' or type == 'tal' then
        if dir == 'r' then outPos['x'] = dialSpacing
        else outPos['x'] = -1*dialSpacing end
        outPos['z'] = 4*dialSpacing

    elseif type == 'koi' then
        if kNum == 1 or kNum == 2 then outPos['x'] = 2*dialSpacing
        else outPos['x'] = -2*dialSpacing end
        if kNum == 1 or kNum == 3 then outPos['z'] = 4*dialSpacing
        else outPos['z'] = 5*dialSpacing end
        kNum = kNum + 1

    else
        if type == 'b' then outPos['x'] = dialSpacing
        elseif type == 't' then outPos['x'] = 2*dialSpacing
        end

        if dir == 'e' or dir == 'l' then outPos['x'] = outPos['x'] * -1 end
    end

    if z_half == 1 then
        outPos['x'] = outPos['x'] * -1
        outPos['y'] = outPos['y'] * -1
        outPos['z'] = outPos['z'] * -1
    end


    outPos['x'] = outPos['x'] + te0pos['x'] - (2*dialSpacing*z_half)
    outPos['y'] = outPos['y'] + te0pos['y']
    outPos['z'] = outPos['z'] + te0pos['z']
    return outPos
end

function offset(table1, table2)
    return {table1[1]+table2[1], table1[2]+table2[2], table1[3]+table2[3]}
end

-- RETURN A ROTATION THAT IS NATURAL TO A PLAYER IN CERTAIN QUADRANT
-- FACEUP OR FACEDOWN
function correctQuadrantRotation(z_halfRot, faceup)
    if z_halfRot > 0 then
        if faceup == false then return {x=180, y=180, z=0}
        else return {x=0, y=0, z=0} end
    else
        if faceup == false then return {x=180, y=0, z=0}
        else return {x=0, y=180, z=0} end
    end
end

function init()
    self.setRotation(offset(self.getRotation(), {180, 180, 0}))
    if(self.getPosition()[1] < 0) then x_half = -1 else x_half = 1 end
    if(self.getPosition()[3] < 0) then z_half = -1 else z_half = 1 end
    local dialSpacing = (2/0.625)*(self.getScale()[1])
    self.setRotation(correctQuadrantRotation(z_half, false))
    local te0pos = self.getPosition()
    originPos = te0pos
    local stackDials = self.getObjects()
    local dialNum = 0
    for k, dial in pairs(stackDials) do
        if dial['description'] ~= 'spec' then
            local dialPos = decodePos(dial['description'], te0pos, dialSpacing)
            newDial = self.takeObject({position=dialPos, rotation=correctQuadrantRotation(z_half, true), guid=dial['guid']})
            newDial.setPosition(dialPos)
            newDial.setRotation(correctQuadrantRotation(z_half, true))
        end
    end
    local spos = self.getPosition()
    if z_half == -1 then self.setPosition({spos[1]+(3*dialSpacing), spos[2], spos[3]+(5*dialSpacing)})
    else self.setPosition({spos[1]-(3*dialSpacing), spos[2], spos[3]-(5*dialSpacing)}) end
    -- spawnResetButton()
    self.destruct()
end

-- -- DIAL SPACING - DEPENDENT ON SCALE
function decodePos(desc, te0pos, dialSpacing)
    dir = nil
    speed = nil
    type = nil
    if desc:sub(-1, -1) == 's' then
        type = 'seg'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(-2, -2))
        dir = desc:sub(-3, -3)
    elseif desc:sub(-1, -1) == 't' then
        type = 'tal'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(-2, -2))
        dir = desc:sub(-3, -3)
    elseif desc:sub(1, 1) == 'k' then
        type = 'koi'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(2, 2))
        dir = 's'
    elseif desc:sub(1, 1) == 's' then
        type = 's'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(2, 2))
        dir = 's'
    else
        type = desc:sub(1, 1)
        dir = desc:sub(2, 2)
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(3, 3))
    end

    outPos = {x=0, y=0.1, z=0}
    outPos['z'] = speed * dialSpacing
    if type == 's' then outPos['x'] = 0

    elseif type == 'seg' or type == 'tal' then
        if dir == 'r' then outPos['x'] = dialSpacing
        else outPos['x'] = -1*dialSpacing end
        outPos['z'] = 4*dialSpacing

    elseif type == 'koi' then
        if kNum == 1 or kNum == 2 then outPos['x'] = 2*dialSpacing
        else outPos['x'] = -2*dialSpacing end
        if kNum == 1 or kNum == 3 then outPos['z'] = 4*dialSpacing
        else outPos['z'] = 5*dialSpacing end
        kNum = kNum + 1

    else
        if type == 'b' then outPos['x'] = dialSpacing
        elseif type == 't' then outPos['x'] = 2*dialSpacing
        end

        if dir == 'e' or dir == 'l' then outPos['x'] = outPos['x'] * -1 end
    end

    if z_half == 1 then
        outPos['x'] = outPos['x'] * -1
        outPos['y'] = outPos['y'] * -1
        outPos['z'] = outPos['z'] * -1
    end


    outPos['x'] = outPos['x'] + te0pos['x'] - (2*dialSpacing*z_half)
    outPos['y'] = outPos['y'] + te0pos['y']
    outPos['z'] = outPos['z'] + te0pos['z']
    return outPos
end

function offset(table1, table2)
    return {table1[1]+table2[1], table1[2]+table2[2], table1[3]+table2[3]}
end

-- RETURN A ROTATION THAT IS NATURAL TO A PLAYER IN CERTAIN QUADRANT
-- FACEUP OR FACEDOWN
function correctQuadrantRotation(z_halfRot, faceup)
    if z_halfRot > 0 then
        if faceup == false then return {x=180, y=180, z=0}
        else return {x=0, y=0, z=0} end
    else
        if faceup == false then return {x=180, y=0, z=0}
        else return {x=0, y=180, z=0} end
    end
end

function init()
    self.setRotation(offset(self.getRotation(), {180, 180, 0}))
    if(self.getPosition()[1] < 0) then x_half = -1 else x_half = 1 end
    if(self.getPosition()[3] < 0) then z_half = -1 else z_half = 1 end
    local dialSpacing = (2/0.625)*(self.getScale()[1])
    self.setRotation(correctQuadrantRotation(z_half, false))
    local te0pos = self.getPosition()
    originPos = te0pos
    local stackDials = self.getObjects()
    local dialNum = 0
    for k, dial in pairs(stackDials) do
        if dial['description'] ~= 'spec' then
            local dialPos = decodePos(dial['description'], te0pos, dialSpacing)
            newDial = self.takeObject({position=dialPos, rotation=correctQuadrantRotation(z_half, true), guid=dial['guid']})
            newDial.setPosition(dialPos)
            newDial.setRotation(correctQuadrantRotation(z_half, true))
        end
    end
    local spos = self.getPosition()
    if z_half == -1 then self.setPosition({spos[1]+(3*dialSpacing), spos[2], spos[3]+(5*dialSpacing)})
    else self.setPosition({spos[1]-(3*dialSpacing), spos[2], spos[3]-(5*dialSpacing)}) end
    -- spawnResetButton()
    self.destruct()
end

    self.setRotation({sRot['x']+180, sRot['y']+180, sRot['z']})
end

-- RETURN POSITION BASED ON:
-- -- DESCRIPTION (WHICH MOVE IT IS)
-- -- "TURN LEFT ZERO" POSITION, OFFSET
-- -- DIAL SPACING - DEPENDENT ON SCALE
function decodePos(desc, te0pos, dialSpacing)
    dir = nil
    speed = nil
    type = nil
    if desc:sub(-1, -1) == 's' then
        type = 'seg'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(-2, -2))
        dir = desc:sub(-3, -3)
    elseif desc:sub(-1, -1) == 't' then
        type = 'tal'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(-2, -2))
        dir = desc:sub(-3, -3)
    elseif desc:sub(1, 1) == 'k' then
        type = 'koi'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(2, 2))
        dir = 's'
    elseif desc:sub(1, 1) == 's' then
        type = 's'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(2, 2))
        dir = 's'
    else
        type = desc:sub(1, 1)
        dir = desc:sub(2, 2)
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(3, 3))
    end

    outPos = {x=0, y=0.1, z=0}
    outPos['z'] = speed * dialSpacing
    if type == 's' then outPos['x'] = 0

    elseif type == 'seg' or type == 'tal' then
        if dir == 'r' then outPos['x'] = dialSpacing
        else outPos['x'] = -1*dialSpacing end
        outPos['z'] = 4*dialSpacing

    elseif type == 'koi' then
        if kNum == 1 or kNum == 2 then outPos['x'] = 2*dialSpacing
        else outPos['x'] = -2*dialSpacing end
        if kNum == 1 or kNum == 3 then outPos['z'] = 4*dialSpacing
        else outPos['z'] = 5*dialSpacing end
        kNum = kNum + 1

    else
        if type == 'b' then outPos['x'] = dialSpacing
        elseif type == 't' then outPos['x'] = 2*dialSpacing
        end

        if dir == 'e' or dir == 'l' then outPos['x'] = outPos['x'] * -1 end
    end

    if z_half == 1 then
        outPos['x'] = outPos['x'] * -1
        outPos['y'] = outPos['y'] * -1
        outPos['z'] = outPos['z'] * -1
    end


    outPos['x'] = outPos['x'] + te0pos['x'] - (2*dialSpacing*z_half)
    outPos['y'] = outPos['y'] + te0pos['y']
    outPos['z'] = outPos['z'] + te0pos['z']
    return outPos
end

function offset(table1, table2)
    return {table1[1]+table2[1], table1[2]+table2[2], table1[3]+table2[3]}
end

-- RETURN A ROTATION THAT IS NATURAL TO A PLAYER IN CERTAIN QUADRANT
-- FACEUP OR FACEDOWN
function correctQuadrantRotation(z_halfRot, faceup)
    if z_halfRot > 0 then
        if faceup == false then return {x=180, y=180, z=0}
        else return {x=0, y=0, z=0} end
    else
        if faceup == false then return {x=180, y=0, z=0}
        else return {x=0, y=180, z=0} end
    end
end

function init()
    self.setRotation(offset(self.getRotation(), {180, 180, 0}))
    if(self.getPosition()[1] < 0) then x_half = -1 else x_half = 1 end
    if(self.getPosition()[3] < 0) then z_half = -1 else z_half = 1 end
    local dialSpacing = (2/0.625)*(self.getScale()[1])
    self.setRotation(correctQuadrantRotation(z_half, false))
    local te0pos = self.getPosition()
    originPos = te0pos
    local stackDials = self.getObjects()
    local dialNum = 0
    for k, dial in pairs(stackDials) do
        if dial['description'] ~= 'spec' then
            local dialPos = decodePos(dial['description'], te0pos, dialSpacing)
            newDial = self.takeObject({position=dialPos, rotation=correctQuadrantRotation(z_half, true), guid=dial['guid']})
            newDial.setPosition(dialPos)
            newDial.setRotation(correctQuadrantRotation(z_half, true))
        end
    end
    local spos = self.getPosition()
    if z_half == -1 then self.setPosition({spos[1]+(3*dialSpacing), spos[2], spos[3]+(5*dialSpacing)})
    else self.setPosition({spos[1]-(3*dialSpacing), spos[2], spos[3]-(5*dialSpacing)}) end
    -- spawnResetButton()
    self.destruct()
end

    if z_halfRot > 0 then
        if faceup == false then return {x=180, y=180, z=0}
        else return {x=0, y=0, z=0} end
    else
        if faceup == false then return {x=180, y=0, z=0}
        else return {x=0, y=180, z=0} end
    end

-- -- DESCRIPTION (WHICH MOVE IT IS)
-- -- "TURN LEFT ZERO" POSITION, OFFSET
-- -- DIAL SPACING - DEPENDENT ON SCALE
function decodePos(desc, te0pos, dialSpacing)
    dir = nil
    speed = nil
    type = nil
    if desc:sub(-1, -1) == 's' then
        type = 'seg'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(-2, -2))
        dir = desc:sub(-3, -3)
    elseif desc:sub(-1, -1) == 't' then
        type = 'tal'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(-2, -2))
        dir = desc:sub(-3, -3)
    elseif desc:sub(1, 1) == 'k' then
        type = 'koi'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(2, 2))
        dir = 's'
    elseif desc:sub(1, 1) == 's' then
        type = 's'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(2, 2))
        dir = 's'
    else
        type = desc:sub(1, 1)
        dir = desc:sub(2, 2)
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(3, 3))
    end

    outPos = {x=0, y=0.1, z=0}
    outPos['z'] = speed * dialSpacing
    if type == 's' then outPos['x'] = 0

    elseif type == 'seg' or type == 'tal' then
        if dir == 'r' then outPos['x'] = dialSpacing
        else outPos['x'] = -1*dialSpacing end
        outPos['z'] = 4*dialSpacing

    elseif type == 'koi' then
        if kNum == 1 or kNum == 2 then outPos['x'] = 2*dialSpacing
        else outPos['x'] = -2*dialSpacing end
        if kNum == 1 or kNum == 3 then outPos['z'] = 4*dialSpacing
        else outPos['z'] = 5*dialSpacing end
        kNum = kNum + 1

        elseif type == 't' then outPos['x'] = 2*dialSpacing
        end

        outPos['x'] = outPos['x'] * -1
        outPos['y'] = outPos['y'] * -1
        outPos['z'] = outPos['z'] * -1
    end


    outPos['x'] = outPos['x'] + te0pos['x'] - (2*dialSpacing*z_half)
    outPos['y'] = outPos['y'] + te0pos['y']
    outPos['z'] = outPos['z'] + te0pos['z']
    return outPos
end

x_half = 0          -- which half of table X-axis-wise we play on (+1 or -1)
z_half = 0          -- which half of table Z-axis-wise we play on (+1 or -1)
kNum = 1            -- koiogran turn counter (for layout)

-- SPAWN FLIP AND LAYOUT BUTTONS
function onLoad()
    self.unlock()
    local button = {}
    button.click_function = 'init'
    button.function_owner = self
    button.label = 'Lay out'
    button.position = {0, -0.5, 0}
    button.rotation = {180, 180, 0}
    button.width = 1500
    button.height = 500
    button.font_size = 300
    self.createButton(button)
    button.width = 1800
    button.click_function = 'selfFlip'
    button.label = 'Flip to start'
    button.rotation = {0, 0, 0}
    button.position = {0, 0.5, 0}
    self.createButton(button)
end

function selfFlip()
    local sRot = self.getRotation()
    self.setRotation({sRot['x']+180, sRot['y']+180, sRot['z']})
end

-- RETURN POSITION BASED ON:
-- -- DESCRIPTION (WHICH MOVE IT IS)
-- -- "TURN LEFT ZERO" POSITION, OFFSET
-- -- DIAL SPACING - DEPENDENT ON SCALE
function decodePos(desc, te0pos, dialSpacing)
    dir = nil
    speed = nil
    type = nil
    if desc:sub(-1, -1) == 's' then
        type = 'seg'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(-2, -2))
        dir = desc:sub(-3, -3)
    elseif desc:sub(-1, -1) == 't' then
        type = 'tal'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(-2, -2))
        dir = desc:sub(-3, -3)
    elseif desc:sub(1, 1) == 'k' then
        type = 'koi'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(2, 2))
        dir = 's'
    elseif desc:sub(1, 1) == 's' then
        type = 's'
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(2, 2))
        dir = 's'
    else
        type = desc:sub(1, 1)
        dir = desc:sub(2, 2)
        speed = tonumber(desc:sub(3, 3))
    end

    outPos = {x=0, y=0.1, z=0}
    outPos['z'] = speed * dialSpacing
    if type == 's' then outPos['x'] = 0

    elseif type == 'seg' or type == 'tal' then
        if dir == 'r' then outPos['x'] = dialSpacing
        else outPos['x'] = -1*dialSpacing end
        outPos['z'] = 4*dialSpacing

    elseif type == 'koi' then
        if kNum == 1 or kNum == 2 then outPos['x'] = 2*dialSpacing
        else outPos['x'] = -2*dialSpacing end
        if kNum == 1 or kNum == 3 then outPos['z'] = 4*dialSpacing
        else outPos['z'] = 5*dialSpacing end
        kNum = kNum + 1

    else
        if type == 'b' then outPos['x'] = dialSpacing
        elseif type == 't' then outPos['x'] = 2*dialSpacing
        end

        if dir == 'e' or dir == 'l' then outPos['x'] = outPos['x'] * -1 end
    end

    if z_half == 1 then
        outPos['x'] = outPos['x'] * -1
        outPos['y'] = outPos['y'] * -1
        outPos['z'] = outPos['z'] * -1
    end


    outPos['x'] = outPos['x'] + te0pos['x'] - (2*dialSpacing*z_half)
    outPos['y'] = outPos['y'] + te0pos['y']
    outPos['z'] = outPos['z'] + te0pos['z']
    return outPos
end

function offset(table1, table2)
    return {table1[1]+table2[1], table1[2]+table2[2], table1[3]+table2[3]}
end

-- RETURN A ROTATION THAT IS NATURAL TO A PLAYER IN CERTAIN QUADRANT
-- FACEUP OR FACEDOWN
function correctQuadrantRotation(z_halfRot, faceup)
    if z_halfRot > 0 then
        if faceup == false then return {x=180, y=180, z=0}
        else return {x=0, y=0, z=0} end
    else
        if faceup == false then return {x=180, y=0, z=0}
        else return {x=0, y=180, z=0} end
    end
end

function init()
    self.setRotation(offset(self.getRotation(), {180, 180, 0}))
    if(self.getPosition()[1] < 0) then x_half = -1 else x_half = 1 end
    if(self.getPosition()[3] < 0) then z_half = -1 else z_half = 1 end
    local dialSpacing = (2/0.625)*(self.getScale()[1])
    self.setRotation(correctQuadrantRotation(z_half, false))
    local te0pos = self.getPosition()
    originPos = te0pos
    local stackDials = self.getObjects()
    local dialNum = 0
    for k, dial in pairs(stackDials) do
        if dial['description'] ~= 'spec' then
            local dialPos = decodePos(dial['description'], te0pos, dialSpacing)
            newDial = self.takeObject({position=dialPos, rotation=correctQuadrantRotation(z_half, true), guid=dial['guid']})
            newDial.setPosition(dialPos)
            newDial.setRotation(correctQuadrantRotation(z_half, true))
        end
    end
    local spos = self.getPosition()
    if z_half == -1 then self.setPosition({spos[1]+(3*dialSpacing), spos[2], spos[3]+(5*dialSpacing)})
    else self.setPosition({spos[1]-(3*dialSpacing), spos[2], spos[3]-(5*dialSpacing)}) end
    -- spawnResetButton()
    self.destruct()
end
